[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-use-after-free vulnerability has been detected in the Wireshark telnet [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdissector [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`packet-telnet.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during fuzzing tests. The issue involves a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite operation attempting to access memory at address `[0m[1;36m0x51c000000880[0m[39m` that has [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready been freed. The vulnerability is triggered during the dissection of telnet [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackets when processing NAWS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNegotiate About Window Size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m suboptions.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe AddressSanitizer has detected a heap-use-after-free error with a scariness [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscore of [0m[1;36m46[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte-write-heap-use-after-free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This is a critical memory safety [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue where the code attempts to write to memory that has already been deallocated.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Heap-Use-After-Free [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUAF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: This vulnerability occurs when a program continues [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto use a pointer after the memory it points to has been freed. This can lead to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes, memory corruption, or potentially arbitrary code execution if exploited.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Write Operation Location**: The error occurs during a `memcpy` operation in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `tvb_memcpy` function, specifically when calling `tvb_get_raw_bytes_as_stringz`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom the `telnet_add_text` function at line [0m[1;36m2211[0m[39m of `packet-telnet.c`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory Lifecycle**:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Allocation**: Memory [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1920[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was allocated via `g_malloc` in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`dissect_naws_subopt` function at line [0m[1;36m652[0m[39m of `packet-telnet.c`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Deallocation**: The same memory was freed via `wmem_simple_free` in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`telnet_sub_option` function at line [0m[1;36m2099[0m[39m of `packet-telnet.c`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Invalid Access**: After freeing, the code attempts to write to this freed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory through the `telnet_add_text` function at line [0m[1;36m2211[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Call Flow Analysis**:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The dissection process starts in `dissect_telnet` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2322[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It calls `telnet_command` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2182[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Which then calls `telnet_sub_option` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2099[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - where the memory is freed[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Later, `dissect_telnet` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2337[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls `telnet_add_text` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m2211[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the freed memory is accessed[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Triggering Input**: The fuzzer discovered this issue with a specific input [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   \[0m[1;36m377[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m372[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m037[0m[39m\000P\[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m030[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m377[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m360[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m377[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m372[0m[39m\"\[0m[1;36m001[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m001[0m[39m\[0m[1;36m377[0m[39m\360aaaa[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a comprehensive understanding of this issue, the following code sections [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be examined:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`epan/dissectors/packet-telnet.c`**:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m652[0m[39m: `dissect_naws_subopt` - where memory allocation occurs[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m2099[0m[39m: `telnet_sub_option` - where memory deallocation occurs[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m2182[0m[39m: `telnet_command` - intermediate function in the call chain[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m2211[0m[39m: `telnet_add_text` - where the use-after-free access occurs[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m2322[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m2337[0m[39m: `dissect_telnet` - the main dissection function [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcoordinating these calls[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory Management**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between `g_malloc` and `wmem_simple_free`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The lifetime management of telnet suboption data structures[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How telnet text data references are maintained across different dissection [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mphases[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Buffer Management in `epan/tvbuff.c`**:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m945[0m[39m: `tvb_memcpy` - the actual memory copy operation[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Lines [0m[1;36m4047[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m4073[0m[39m: `tvb_get_raw_bytes_as_stringz` functions that attempt to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess the freed memory[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **State Management**:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How telnet dissector maintains state between processing suboptions and adding [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtext[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are assumptions about data persistence that are violated[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue appears to be a timing problem where memory allocated for processing a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNAWS suboption is freed prematurely, but pointers or references to that memory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain in use by subsequent processing stages, particularly when adding telnet text[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the dissection tree.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2213[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2214[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2215[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2216[0m[39m:     * In Telnet, CR NUL is the way you send a CR by itself in the[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2217[0m[39m:     * default ASCII mode; don't treat CR by itself as a line ending,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2218[0m[39m:     * treat only CR NUL, CR LF, or LF by itself as a line ending.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2219[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2220[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext_offset == offset + linelen + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m && len >= [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2221[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2222[0m[39m:       * Well, we saw a one-character line ending, so either it's a CR[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2223[0m[39m:       * or an LF; we have at least two characters left, including the[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2224[0m[39m:       * CR.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2225[0m[39m:       *[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2226[0m[39m:       * If the line ending is a CR, skip all subsequent CRs; at[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2227[0m[39m:       * least one capture appeared to have multiple CRs at the end of[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2228[0m[39m:       * a line.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2216[0m[39m:     * In Telnet, CR NUL is the way you send a CR by itself in the[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2217[0m[39m:     * default ASCII mode; don't treat CR by itself as a line ending,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2218[0m[39m:     * treat only CR NUL, CR LF, or LF by itself as a line ending.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2219[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2220[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext_offset == offset + linelen + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m && len >= [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2222[0m[39m:       * Well, we saw a one-character line ending, so either it's a CR[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2223[0m[39m:       * or an LF; we have at least two characters left, including the[0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2216[0m[39m:     * In Telnet, CR NUL is the way you send a CR by itself in the[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2217[0m[39m:     * default ASCII mode; don't treat CR by itself as a line ending,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2218[0m[39m:     * treat only CR NUL, CR LF, or LF by itself as a line ending.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2219[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2220[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext_offset == offset + linelen + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m && len >= [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2221[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2222[0m[39m:       * Well, we saw a one-character line ending, so either it's a CR[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2223[0m[39m:       * or an LF; we have at least two characters left, including the[0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mepan/dissectors/packet-telnet.[0m[1;92mc:2200[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2230[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2200[0m[39m:     * Find the end of the line.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2201[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2205[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Telnet RFC [0m[1;36m1184[0m[39m allows for specifying window size via columns and [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2209[0m[39m:   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m hf_telnet_naws_subopt_set [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2210[0m[39m:    int start_offset = hf_telnet_width * hf_telnet_line;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2211[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mtvb_get_raw_bytes_as_stringz[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtvb, offset, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlinelen < hf_telnet_width[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlinelen : hf_telnet_width, hf_naws_data + start_offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2212[0m[39m:    hf_telnet_line = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhf_telnet_line + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m % hf_telnet_height;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2213[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2214[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2215[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2216[0m[39m:     * In Telnet, CR NUL is the way you send a CR by itself in the[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2217[0m[39m:     * default ASCII mode; don't treat CR by itself as a line ending,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2218[0m[39m:     * treat only CR NUL, CR LF, or LF by itself as a line ending.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2219[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2220[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext_offset == offset + linelen + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m && len >= [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2221[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2222[0m[39m:       * Well, we saw a one-character line ending, so either it's a CR[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2223[0m[39m:       * or an LF; we have at least two characters left, including the[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2224[0m[39m:       * CR.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2225[0m[39m:       *[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2226[0m[39m:       * If the line ending is a CR, skip all subsequent CRs; at[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2227[0m[39m:       * least one capture appeared to have multiple CRs at the end of[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2228[0m[39m:       * a line.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
